<paragraph blockId="36.[402,913,1615,1642]" box="[402,913,1615,1642]" pageId="36" pageNumber="835">
<heading box="[402,913,1615,1642]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="36" pageNumber="835" reason="5">
<taxonomicName authority="(Cranston, 2007)" baseAuthorityName="Cranston" baseAuthorityYear="2007" box="[402,913,1615,1642]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Tanytarsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="835" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bromelicola">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[402,702,1615,1642]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="835">Tanytarsus bromelicola</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Cranston PS" box="[718,904,1615,1642]" pageId="36" pageNumber="835" pagination="617 - 622" refId="ref23777" refString="Cranston PS. 2007. A new species for a bromeliad phytotelm-dwelling Tanytarsus (Diptera: Chironomidae). Ann Entomol Soc Am. 100 (5): 617 - 622. doi: 10.1603 / 0013 - 8746 (2007) 100 [617: ANSFAB] 2.0. CO; 2." type="journal article" year="2007">Cranston, 2007</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[160,1155,1669,1728]" box="[192,1155,1669,1694]" pageId="36" pageNumber="835">This chironomid is a predator and was found in ornamental bromeliad phytotelmata in</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="37" lastPageNumber="836" pageId="36" pageNumber="835" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="36.[160,1155,1669,1728]" lastBlockId="37.[160,1156,142,306]" lastPageId="37" lastPageNumber="836" pageId="36" pageNumber="835">
Mahogany Run on St. Thomas. This is the only species in the genus known from bromeliads, and is reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[545,675,142,167]" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Puerto Rico</collectingCountry>
and Florida (
<bibRefCitation author="Cranston PS" box="[827,993,142,167]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" pagination="617 - 622" refId="ref23777" refString="Cranston PS. 2007. A new species for a bromeliad phytotelm-dwelling Tanytarsus (Diptera: Chironomidae). Ann Entomol Soc Am. 100 (5): 617 - 622. doi: 10.1603 / 0013 - 8746 (2007) 100 [617: ANSFAB] 2.0. CO; 2." type="journal article" year="2007">Cranston 2007</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Miller AC" box="[1014,1156,142,167]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" pagination="391 - 396" refId="ref27369" refString="Miller AC. 1971. Observations on the Chironomidae (Diptera) inhabiting the leaf axils of two species of Bromeliaceae on St. John, US Virgin Islands. Can Entomol. 103 (3): 391 - 396. doi: 10.4039 / Ent 103391 - 3." type="journal article" year="1971">Miller (1971)</bibRefCitation>
identified a chironomid from St. John bromeliads as possibly 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Malloch" authorityYear="1915" box="[904,1031,177,202]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Tanytarsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confusus">
<emphasis box="[904,1031,177,202]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">T. confusus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Cranston PS" box="[160,339,212,237]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" pagination="617 - 622" refId="ref23777" refString="Cranston PS. 2007. A new species for a bromeliad phytotelm-dwelling Tanytarsus (Diptera: Chironomidae). Ann Entomol Soc Am. 100 (5): 617 - 622. doi: 10.1603 / 0013 - 8746 (2007) 100 [617: ANSFAB] 2.0. CO; 2." type="journal article" year="2007">Cranston (2007)</bibRefCitation>
argues the identification was likely mistaken and those specimens were 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Cranston" baseAuthorityYear="2007" box="[160,314,246,271]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Tanytarsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bromelicola">
<emphasis box="[160,314,246,271]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">T. bromelicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. As such, this is the first confirmed record of this species from the 
<collectingCountry name="Virgin Islands" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Virgin Islands</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[160,1155,350,479]" box="[160,491,350,376]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,491,350,376]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">
Odontomyia 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,321,350,376]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">/</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1914" box="[322,480,350,376]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Hedriodiscus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Hedriodiscus</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[479,491,350,376]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">?</emphasis>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[160,1155,350,479]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">
Little is known about the 
<taxonomicName box="[482,638,385,410]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Stratiomyidae</taxonomicName>
of the Caribbean. 
<bibRefCitation author="Curran CH" box="[873,1032,385,410]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" pagination="1 - 118" refId="ref24134" refString="Curran CH. 1928. Insects of Porto Rico and the Virgin Islands: diptera or two-winged flies. Sci Surv Porto Rico Virgin Islands. 11: 1 - 118." type="journal article" year="1928">Curran (1928)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Curran" authorityYear="1928" box="[160,366,420,445]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Nemotelus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thomae">
<emphasis box="[160,366,420,445]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Nemotelus thomae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from saline pools on St. Thomas. We collected early instar stratiomyid larvae from freshwater in Bolongo pond, from dense marginal vegetation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[160,1155,523,653]" box="[160,326,523,549]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Newman" authorityYear="1835" box="[160,326,523,549]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,326,523,549]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Cecidomyidae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[160,1155,523,653]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">
Unidentified larvae of this family were found on St. Thomas at the University of the 
<collectingCountry name="Virgin Islands" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Virgin Islands</collectingCountry>
in moss clumps in a concrete drainage behind the Classroom Administration Building.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[160,1156,697,1138]" box="[160,293,697,723]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zetterstedt" authorityYear="1837" box="[160,293,697,723]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,293,697,723]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Ephydridae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[160,1156,697,1138]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">
Unidentified larvae from the subfamily 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zetterstedt" authorityYear="1837" box="[612,739,732,757]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ephydrinae">Ephydrinae</taxonomicName>
were found in bromeliads from the Yacht Haven Grande Marina. Species in this family known from the US Virgin Islands, include 
<taxonomicName authority="Loew, 1878" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1878" box="[253,618,802,827]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Paralimna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decipiens">
<emphasis box="[253,475,802,827]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Paralimna decipiens</emphasis>
Loew, 1878
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Williston, 1896" authorityName="Williston" authorityYear="1896" box="[631,925,802,827]" class="Insecta" family="Nepidae" genus="Ranatra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis box="[631,746,802,827]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">P. obscura</emphasis>
Williston, 1896
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Cresson, 1941" authorityName="Cresson" authorityYear="1941" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Discocerina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavipes">
<emphasis box="[939,1155,802,827]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Discocerina flavipes</emphasis>
Cresson, 1941
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fallen, 1813)" baseAuthorityName="Fallen" baseAuthorityYear="1813" box="[329,731,836,861]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Discocerina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscurella">
<emphasis box="[329,571,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Discocerina obscurella</emphasis>
(Fall√©n, 1813)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Loew, 1862)" baseAuthorityName="Loew" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[742,1152,836,861]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Cressonomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aciculata">
<emphasis box="[742,999,836,861]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Cressonomyia aciculata</emphasis>
(Loew, 1862)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Williston, 1896" authorityName="Williston" authorityYear="1896" box="[160,533,871,896]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Discomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dubia">
<emphasis box="[160,350,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Discomyza dubia</emphasis>
Williston, 1896
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wiedemann, 1824)" baseAuthorityName="Wiedemann" baseAuthorityYear="1824" box="[548,1056,871,896]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Discomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculipennis">
<emphasis box="[548,820,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Discomyza maculipennis</emphasis>
(Wiedemann, 1824)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Williston, 1987)" baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1987" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Parydra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="humilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Parydra humilis</emphasis>
(Williston, 1987)
</taxonomicName>
and an unidentified species of 
<taxonomicName box="[806,906,906,931]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Ochthera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[806,906,906,931]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Ochthera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Curran CH" box="[923,1066,906,931]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" pagination="1 - 118" refId="ref24134" refString="Curran CH. 1928. Insects of Porto Rico and the Virgin Islands: diptera or two-winged flies. Sci Surv Porto Rico Virgin Islands. 11: 1 - 118." type="journal article" year="1928">Curran 1928</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Barber HG" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" pagination="264 - 441" refId="ref22283" refString="Barber HG. 1939. Insects of Porto Rico and the Virgin Islands: Hemiptera-Heteroptera (excepting the Miridae and Corixidae). Sci Surv Porto Rico Virgin Islands. 14: 264 - 441." type="journal article" year="1939">Barber 1939</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Mathis WN" box="[231,371,940,965]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" pagination="1 - 77" refId="ref26965" refString="Mathis WN. 1997. Shore Flies of the Belizean Cays (Diptera: Ephydridae). Smithson Contrib Zool. 592: 1 - 77. doi: 10.5479 / si. 00810282.592." type="journal article" year="1997">Mathis 1997</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ale-Rocha R &amp; Mathis WN" box="[386,703,940,965]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" pagination="1 - 149" refId="ref22105" refString="Ale-Rocha R, Mathis WN. 2015. A revision of the New World species of Paralimna Loew (Diptera: Ephydridae). Smithson Contrib Zool. 643: 1 - 149." type="journal article" year="2015">Ale-Rocha and Mathis 2015</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Mathis WN &amp; Rodrigues FDA Jr. &amp; Couri MS" box="[718,926,940,965]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" pagination="752 - 770" refId="ref27000" refString="Mathis WN, Rodrigues FDA Jr., Couri MS. 2016. Family Ephydridae. Zootaxa. 4122 (1): 752 - 770. doi: 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4122.1.64." type="journal article" year="2016">Mathis et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wiedemann, 1830)" authorityName="Ale-Rocha and Mathis" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Wiedemann" baseAuthorityYear="1830" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Paralimna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thomae">
<emphasis box="[949,1155,940,965]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Paralimna thomae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Wiedemann CRW" box="[166,371,975,1000]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" refId="ref31761" refString="Wiedemann CRW. 1830. Aussereuropaische zweiflugelige Insecten, Vol. 2. Hamm (GER): Schulz; p. 648." type="journal volume" year="1830">Wiedemann, 1830</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
was originally described from St. Thomas (as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wiedemann" authorityYear="1830" box="[893,1073,975,1000]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" genus="Ephydra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thomae">
<emphasis box="[893,1073,975,1000]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Ephydra thomae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and is the most widespread member of the genus in the Americas (
<bibRefCitation author="Ale-Rocha R &amp; Mathis WN" box="[836,1142,1009,1034]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" pagination="1 - 149" refId="ref22105" refString="Ale-Rocha R, Mathis WN. 2015. A revision of the New World species of Paralimna Loew (Diptera: Ephydridae). Smithson Contrib Zool. 643: 1 - 149." type="journal article" year="2015">Ale-Rocha and Mathis 2015</bibRefCitation>
). Several other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zetterstedt" authorityYear="1837" box="[318,445,1044,1069]" class="Insecta" family="Ephydridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Ephydridae</taxonomicName>
are known from Puerto Rico and could also occur in the 
<collectingCountry box="[1103,1155,1044,1069]" name="Virgin Islands" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">USVI</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Curran CH" box="[166,309,1079,1104]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" pagination="1 - 118" refId="ref24134" refString="Curran CH. 1928. Insects of Porto Rico and the Virgin Islands: diptera or two-winged flies. Sci Surv Porto Rico Virgin Islands. 11: 1 - 118." type="journal article" year="1928">Curran 1928</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Barber HG" box="[325,464,1079,1104]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" pagination="264 - 441" refId="ref22283" refString="Barber HG. 1939. Insects of Porto Rico and the Virgin Islands: Hemiptera-Heteroptera (excepting the Miridae and Corixidae). Sci Surv Porto Rico Virgin Islands. 14: 264 - 441." type="journal article" year="1939">Barber 1939</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Mathis WN &amp; Zatwarnicki T" box="[481,815,1079,1104]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" pagination="1 - 116" refId="ref27035" refString="Mathis WN, Zatwarnicki T. 2012. A revision of the new world species of Polytrichophora Cresson and Facitrichophora, new genus (Diptera, Ephydridae). ZooKeys. 231: 1 - 116. doi: 10.3897 / zookeys. 231.3687." type="journal article" year="2012">Mathis and Zatwarnicki 2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ale-Rocha R &amp; Mathis WN" box="[832,1150,1079,1104]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" pagination="1 - 149" refId="ref22105" refString="Ale-Rocha R, Mathis WN. 2015. A revision of the New World species of Paralimna Loew (Diptera: Ephydridae). Smithson Contrib Zool. 643: 1 - 149." type="journal article" year="2015">Ale-Rocha and Mathis 2015</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Mathis WN &amp; Rodrigues FDA Jr. &amp; Couri MS" box="[160,359,1113,1138]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" pagination="752 - 770" refId="ref27000" refString="Mathis WN, Rodrigues FDA Jr., Couri MS. 2016. Family Ephydridae. Zootaxa. 4122 (1): 752 - 770. doi: 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4122.1.64." type="journal article" year="2016">Mathis et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[160,1156,1182,1555]" box="[160,278,1182,1208]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">
<taxonomicName box="[160,278,1182,1208]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,278,1182,1208]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Syrphidae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[160,1156,1182,1555]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">
Unidentified larvae were found on St. Thomas in brackish pools with decomposing vegetation in the mangroves at Magens Beach and Red Hook. A freshwater form very similar to 
<emphasis box="[271,346,1287,1312]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Erstalis</emphasis>
sp. was encountered in the dense, rotting vegetation of an embayment part of a small ghut at Raphune Hill (which also had evidence of septic contamination). 
<bibRefCitation author="Curran CH" box="[160,312,1356,1381]" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" pagination="1 - 118" refId="ref24134" refString="Curran CH. 1928. Insects of Porto Rico and the Virgin Islands: diptera or two-winged flies. Sci Surv Porto Rico Virgin Islands. 11: 1 - 118." type="journal article" year="1928">Curran (1928)</bibRefCitation>
reported two species of 
<emphasis box="[589,664,1356,1381]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Erstalis</emphasis>
from St. Thomas. Other syrphid larvae were found in 
<taxonomicName box="[277,485,1391,1416]" class="Liliopsida" family="Heliconiaceae" genus="Heliconia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Zingiberales" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="caribaea">
<emphasis box="[277,485,1391,1416]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="836">Heliconia caribaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[556,797,1391,1416]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Billbergia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="37" pageNumber="836" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pyramidalis">
